%section
  %h2 Introduction

  Some branches of the Penn Libraries use card readers to manage access.
  The card reader records the time of the entrance and the identity of the patron.
  This data is owned by Campus Security and is shared monthly with the Penn Libraries at our request to understand who is visiting and using the spaces within the Penn Libraries.
  For branches that do not have card swipe access, they provide yearly reports of estimates or laser counting to Andrew Sarno.
  Those reports are inconsistent and not represented here.
  Before the renovation of Holman Biotech Commons, they provided monthly counts from 2013 to 2020, these counts are represented in a legacy table for further analysis. 

  %ul
    %li 
      The Overview page describes Library visitation of the general population for all of the fiscal years available.
    %li
      The Populations and Penetration page describes the number and frequency of visitors by school divided into the undergraduate, graduate, and faculty/staff populations. 
    %li
      All plots can be filtered by interacting with the legend.
      Data in the plots are displayed on hover.

